http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/On-a-mission/article14002621.ece

A three-member official team of the Godavari River Management Board (GRMB) established as per the States Reorganisation Act (AP) of 2014 visited the Sriramsagar Project at Pochampad in Balkonda mandal for the first time after its formation, on Saturday.Led by the board chairman Srirama Saran, the team comprising Sameer Chatterji, member secretary and chief engineer M.K. Mathur observed Lakshmi, Kakatiya, Saraswathi canals, flood flow canals, and also the dam.They were closeted with the project engineers and other officials later.